-- Argentina Stock Movers: IRSA, Petrobras Argentina Were Active
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-05-31T22:13:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/argentina-stock-movers-irsa-petrobras-argentina-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the close of trading in
 Buenos Aires . The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.4 percent to 2,256.74.  IRSA Inversiones y Representaciones SA  (IRSA AF), the
Argentine real estate holding company, fell 4.5 percent to 4.20
pesos.  Argentina ’s construction activity fell 7.6 percent in
April from a year ago, the National Statistics and Census
Institute in Buenos Aires said.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)   fell 0.9 percent to 5.45
pesos. The local unit of  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company
Petroleo Brasileiro SA said in a regulatory filing today it will
increase its stake in Petrolera Entre Lomas SA for $249.4
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  